- Yale

In 2015, in response to a White House call to action, Yale signed the 
American Campuses Act on Climate Pledge, 
agreeing to accelerate our transition to low-carbon energy while enhancing sustainable and resilient practices
across the university.
As part of these efforts, Yale’s campus will be carbon-neutral by 2050. 

Yale’s Sustainability Plan 2025 
details our institutional commitment, and recent milestones reflect progress in many areas. 

