-Sustainable Infrastructure

Universities around the world are making sustainable energy a priority in their campus infrastructure,
so new projects are almost always being built with sustainability in mind. These environmental initiatives 
are reducing energy costs,
countering carbon emissions, and making a
visible commitment to sustainability evident to all. 

-Kevin Wildes, president of Loyola University in New Orleans,
 said. “If not the intellectual centers forming futuristic progress, then who will step up to the plate?”
 
